Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Greta Garbo and Jim Henson
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yg2qc
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 18 May 1990
The death of Greta Garbo, the way in which television is prolonging the life of movies, and a eulogy for puppeteer Jim Henson, as discussed by Alistair Cooke.